22/04/2003
TIRANA, Albania -- On Monday (21 April), the opposition Democratic Party demanded the resignation of two ministers over a scandal involving human trafficking. 
According to the party, Minister of Public Order Luan Rama and Minister of Culture, Youth and Sports Arta Dade were involved in efforts to arrange visas for 30 children who were taken to the Netherlands in the guise of a football team. 
The opposition also initiated an inquiry through parliamentary committees to verify similar cases.
Also on Monday, former members of the Social Democratic Party announced the establishment of a new political party, the Social Democracy Party. 
The founders are Paskal Milo, Gjergj Rokaj and Tonin Bala. 
(Koha Jone, Shekulli - 22/04/03; ATA - 21/04/03)
